## 2. Query graphify (mandatory, before searching)

This project has a graphify knowledge graph at `graphify-out/`.

- Before answering architecture or codebase questions, read `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md`
- Query the graph with:
  ```
  DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH=/opt/homebrew/opt/expat/lib ~/.local/bin/graphify query "<question>"
  ```
  before grepping raw code.
- Rebuild happens automatically via `post-commit` git hook. Verify with `graphify hook status`.

## 3. After every push, update {{WIKI_NAME}} (3 steps, no exceptions)

1. Edit the relevant `{{WIKI_PATH}}/entities/<thing>.md` + append to `{{WIKI_PATH}}/log.md`
2. Commit the {{WIKI_NAME}} repo:
   ```
   cd {{WIKI_PATH}} && git add -A && git commit -m "sync: <summary>"
   ```
3. Rebuild graphify:
   ```
   DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH=/opt/homebrew/opt/expat/lib ~/.local/bin/graphify query "rebuild"
   ```

Do not ask. Do not stop after step 1. All three steps, every time.

## 4. Work order

```
graphify -> {{WIKI_NAME}} -> source -> execute -> commit -> push -> edit {{WIKI_NAME}} -> commit {{WIKI_NAME}} -> rebuild graphify
